      <details>
        <summary>What is the Altria dividend?</summary>
        <p>The Altria dividend is the portion of the company's profits (Altria Group, Inc., ticker symbol MO) distributed to its shareholders, traditionally known for being one of the highest yields in the S&P 500.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What is the expected Altria dividend yield 2025?</summary>
        <p>While exact yields fluctuate daily with the stock price, Altria's dividend yield in 2025 has historically remained in the high single digits, typically ranging between 7% and 9%, reflecting the company's commitment to returning cash to shareholders.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What does the Altria dividend history look like?</summary>
        <p>Altria's dividend history is characterized by decades of consistent payouts and frequent increases. Management maintains a target dividend payout ratio of around 80% of its adjusted diluted earnings per share.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Why is the Altria dividend yield so high?</summary>
        <p>The yield is high primarily because the stock price is often depressed due to the systemic risks of the declining tobacco industry. To attract investors despite these headwinds, the company must offer a substantial cash return.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Is the Altria dividend safe?</summary>
        <p>Generally, it is considered secure in the short to medium term due to the company's strong pricing power and massive free cash flow, though long-term safety depends on their success in transitioning to smoke-free alternative products.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
